(
<figureCitation id="C9F62A6A9920FF9A07E14C51A9628255" box="[159,288,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 52" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1201,1224]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,529,1172]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[150,1436,522,1180]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 52. Male terminalia of Hemerodromia isochita sp. nov. 51, lateral view of terminalia; 52, Apex of right ‘ complex process’ situated along inner face of cercus. Abbreviations: cer = cerci, epa = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289950/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 51, 52</figureCitation>
