<subSubSection id="19D765649923FF9907B94F13ADD68117" box="[199,1428,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="517236EF9923FF9907B94F13ADD68117" blockId="34.[151,1436,151,467]" box="[199,1428,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9907B94F13A9048117" bold="true" box="[199,326,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF9905464F13AAD38117" box="[568,657,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isochita">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9905464F13AAD38117" box="[568,657,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">isochita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to this species’ similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF9903654F12AD478117" authority="Smith, 1965" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[1051,1285,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chita">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9903654F12AC378117" box="[1051,1141,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">H. chita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E9923FF9903024F13AD478117" author="Smith" box="[1148,1285,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Smith, K. G. V. (1965) Diptera from Nepal Empididae. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 17 (2), 63 - 112." type="journal article" year="1965">
Smith, 
<number id="E70524C89923FF9903B34F13AD478117" box="[1229,1285,260,285]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F9923FF9902374F13ADD28117" box="[1353,1424,260,285]" name="Nepal" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Nepal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19D765649923FF9907B94F30AD1E81D9" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="517236EF9923FF9907B94F30AD1E81D9" blockId="34.[151,1436,151,467]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9907B94F30A976814A" bold="true" box="[199,308,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks</emphasis>
. The male terminalia are very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF9904734F3EABBF814A" authority="Smith, 1965" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[781,1021,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chita">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9904734F3EAB2B814A" box="[781,873,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">H. chita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E9923FF99040C4F30ABBF814A" author="Smith" box="[882,1021,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Smith, K. G. V. (1965) Diptera from Nepal Empididae. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 17 (2), 63 - 112." type="journal article" year="1965">
Smith, 
<number id="E70524C89923FF9904BB4F30ABBF814A" box="[965,1021,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F9923FF99033B4F30ACCA814A" box="[1093,1160,295,320]" name="Nepal" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Nepal</collectingCountry>
in both colouration and form of cerci and epandrium. Both 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF99055F4F5AAA39816F" box="[545,635,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chita">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF99055F4F5AAA39816F" box="[545,635,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">H. chita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF9905CF4F5AAB6F816F" box="[689,813,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isochita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9905CF4F5AAB6F816F" box="[689,813,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">H. isochita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF99044D4F5BABCE816F" bold="true" box="[819,908,332,357]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A57869923FF99044D4F5BABCE816F" box="[819,908,332,357]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have a distinct ‘stump’ of vein CuA 
<number id="E70524C89923FF99025D4F4CAD698163" box="[1315,1323,347,361]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2.0">2</number>
present in the wing. 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9923FF99066D4F65AA608181" box="[275,546,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isochita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF99066D4F65AA608181" box="[275,546,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Hemerodromia isochita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9923FF9905514F65AACD8181" bold="true" box="[559,655,370,395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A57869923FF9905514F65AACD8181" box="[559,655,370,395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is known only from the mountain Doi Phahompok, Chiang Mai Province, northern 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F9923FF99060C4F81A99481A5" box="[370,470,406,431]" name="Thailand" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="C9F62A6A9923FF9906994F81AA7F81A5" box="[487,573,406,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 82 – 90" captionStartId="48.[151,264,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[292,1274,205,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[277,1305,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURES 82 – 90. Distribution of Hemerodromia spp. in Thailand at a resolution of 0.25 ° and symbols sized to 0.5 ° of latitude and longitude. 82, H. demissa sp. nov.; 83, H. epsilutea sp. nov.; 84, H. etalutea sp. nov.; 85, H. flaviventris Yang &amp; Yang; 86, H. furcata Grootaert, Yang &amp; Saigusa; 87; H. fusca Yang &amp; Yang; 88, H. gammalutea sp. nov.; 89, H. isochita sp. nov.; 90, H. namtokhinpoon sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289960/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number id="E70524C89923FF9905634F80AA7F81A5" box="[541,573,407,431]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
). All but one of the 
<number id="E70524C89923FF9904544F80AB7A81A5" box="[810,824,407,431]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="8.0">8</number>
known specimens were taken in mid-elevation forest (
<quantity id="96359B0A9923FF9907E14FACA8BF81D9" box="[159,253,443,467]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.449" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="1449.0">1,449 m</quantity>
) from May to December with one captured in moist hill evergreen forest at 
<quantity id="96359B0A9923FF99032E4FACACEE81D8" box="[1104,1196,443,467]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="2200.0">2,200 m</quantity>
